  "prompt": "Is every IT company in India the same, in terms of salary, work culture, growth opportunity. Which company is the best to work for as a fresher?",
  "response": "Not all IT companies in India are the same. There are significant differences in:\n\nSalary Ranges:\n- Top-tier: TCS, Infosys, Wipro (\u20b93.5-6 LPA)\n- Mid-tier: Cognizant, HCL, Tech Mahindra (\u20b93-5 LPA)\n- Product companies: Amazon, Google, Microsoft (\u20b98-25 LPA)\n\nWork Culture:\n- Service-based: More structured, repetitive work\n- Product companies: Innovation-driven, challenging projects\n- Startups: Dynamic, less hierarchical\n\nGrowth Opportunities:\n- Service companies: Slower progression\n- Product companies: Faster career growth\n- MNCs: More international exposure\n\nBest Companies for Freshers:\n\nTop Recommendations:\n1. TCS\n- Large campus hiring\n- Good training programs\n- Stable work environment\n\n2. Infosys\n- Excellent learning opportunities\n- Good onboarding process\n- Strong reputation\n\n3. Cognizant\n- Competitive salaries\n- Good skill development\n\nBest Overall:\n- Amazon, Google, Microsoft (if you can crack their interviews)\n- Offer highest salaries\n- Best learning environment\n- Global exposure\n\nRecommendation: Focus on skills, not just company. Continuous learning matters most.",
